post_text:
Ready for another big announcement??

Andrae's Kitchen Food Truck from Walla Walla will be joining us at the Helix Fun Run this year!!! They will be at the park making breakfast even before the fun run begins!! They are bringing a menu of options just in the morning so whether you participate in the fun run or just want to head out with friends and family for an awesome breakfast, it will be a wonderful day in Helix! Did we mention free face painting and balloons for the kids? Save the date and bring your appetite!

shared_text:
Helix Heart of the Country Fun Run‎Helix Heart of the Country Fun Run 2017
May 29, 2017 at 8:18 PM ·

The big day is getting closer! We wanted to do a fun reminder on what the past two year's fun runs provided to our community. For those that don't already know, Helix had major flooding that did a great deal of damage to our town with a large portion of the damage destroying the park. The 2015 Fun Run raised money to purchase a swingset and the 2016 Fun Run added much needed park toys. Let's see how much we can raise in 2017 to keep the improvements coming! The nice thing about the run is you can see exactly where the money went at the Start and Finish line every year. Without all the support, these additions would not be possible. We sincerely thank you!

Helix Heart of the Country Fun Run shared a link to the event: Helix Heart of the Country Fun Run 2017.
May 24, 2017 at 11:01 AM ·

Only 17 Days left until the Fun Run! Have you signed up yet?! Few reminders:

*Helix Market will be open for breakfast at 8 am
*Free face painting for kids
*Walk or Run and feel free to bring those strollers. This is a full family-friendly event
*Pendleton Bottling Company has graciously donated beverages again which will be available at Start/Finish Line and Water Stations along routes
*Custom Trophies made by the Helix Shop Class for make and female 5k/10k age group winners and 1 mile male/female overall winners.
*Helix Pool will be open that day regular hours
*Community Potluck starts at Noon
*We will be adding an additional water station along the race on top of misters
*We will be discussing the Fun Run on the KUMA coffee hour radion station May 31st

Excited to see everyone again this year! If you have any questions feel free to send us a message!

The link to register is: http://heartofthecountry.itsyourrace.com/event.aspx?id=5580

April 20, 2017 at 8:22 AM ·

Exactly 1 Month from today the option to buy a Helix Fun Run Shirt will close. You can still register online before the run and the day of, but the option of buying a shirt prior to the run closes May 20th. Dont miss out!! Fun Fact: a Helix student will be creating the design of the shirts. Plus it will be the same great breathable athletic material as last year's that people were loving. Message us for any questions and we can't wait to see everyone there.

post_text: T-Shirt News: The last day to order Fun Run T-Shirts is May 20th, 2017 to ensure they arrive before Fun Run. They will be the same lightweight athletic material as last year, but new color and Helix Track Team will be designing them again. Get yours ordered before May 20th!! Spread the Word so you don't miss the opportunity. Thanks again everyone for all the support! See you June 10th!

post_text: This year's fun run proceeds will be used for....SHADE! We absolutely love our community pool, but unfortunately we do not have ANY shade which makes it very hard on those that want to spend time at the pool. This year's run proceeds will be helping us purchase much needed Shade Sails for our pool! We cannot wait for people to be able to come to our pool and be able to relax IN or OUT of the SUN if they want! The official event page will be posted soon so keep an eye out and we can't wait to see everyone again this year!

post_text: They're here!!! The toys purchased with the proceeds of the 2016 Helix Fun Run were installed today thanks to Larry and Nick Parker. Thank you to all that participated, donated, and supported this event. Stop by the park and see the new toys because the pictures don't do them justice.
